encode country, gen(country_destring)

encode continent, gen(continent_destring)

encode wave, gen(wave_destring)

*********************************************************************************************************************************************************
* recode depvars for use in probit regression
*********************************************************************************************************************************************************

*recode warwill, 1 for willing to go to war, 0 for no and for 0.5 (depends)
recode warwill (1=1) (0/0.5=0), gen(warwillprobit)


*recode dependent variables to 0 and 1 for use in probit regression, 1 being 10 (never justified, highest level of compliance), 0 being all others, (where non-compliance can somehow be justified)
recode tmorale (10=1) (0/9=0), gen(tmoraleprobit)
recode benefits (10=1) (0/9=0), gen(benefitsprobit)
recode bribecomp (10=1) (0/9=0), gen(bribecompprobit)
recode littermorale (10=1) (0/9=0), gen(littermoraleprobit)
recode drinkdrive (10=1) (0/9=0), gen(drinkdriveprobit)

label var warwillprobit "Willingness to go to War"
label var tmoraleprobit "Tax Morale"
label var benefitsprobit "Benefit Morale"
label var bribecompprobit "Social Norms Against Bribing"
label var littermoraleprobit "Social Norms Against Littering"
label var drinkdriveprobit "Social Norms Against Drunk Driving"


/*for consistency, produce probit variables even though the original vars are coded 0 and 1, with 1 meaning you have ever done it and 0 means otherwise

clonevar environment_petitionprobit = environment_petition
clonevar environment_organizationprobit = environment_organization*/

* recode so 1 = strongly agree, all other categories are in 0
recode increasetaxes_envir (4=1) (0/3=0), gen(increasetaxes_envirprobit)
recode pay20higher_envir (4=1) (0/3=0), gen(pay20higher_envirprobit)

* recode so 1 = active member, 0 and 1 = inactive members and nonmembers
recode members_church (2=1) (0/1=0) , gen(members_churchprobit)
recode members_sport (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_sportprobit)
recode members_art (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_artprobit)
recode members_labour (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_labourprobit)
recode members_political (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_politicalprobit)
recode members_environment (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_environmentprobit)
recode members_professional (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_professionalprobit)
recode members_charitable (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_charitableprobit)
recode members_other (2=1) (0/1=0), gen(members_otherprobit)



* recode so 1 = strongly agree, or the most trust, and all other answers are = 0
recode trust_par (4=1) (0/3=0), gen(trust_parprobit)
recode trust_otherppl (4=1) (0/3=0), gen(trust_otherpplprobit)
* I think it's worth checking trust as a depvar in case of feedback loops between national pride and trust, econometrically it's not ideal but there you go

*********************************************************************************************************************************************************
* recode darkside of national pride depvars (already a 0 and 1 value, no need to change for probit) 
*********************************************************************************************************************************************************

** recode neighbours questions - who would you not like to have as neighbours out of the following
* a124_01 Neighbours: People with a criminal record (0 = not mentioned, 1 = mentioned)
recode a124_01 (-5/-1=.), gen(criminal)

*a124_02 Neighbours: People of a different race
recode a124_02 (-5/-1=.), gen(race)

*a124_03 Neighbours: Heavy drinkers

*a124_04 Neighbours: Emotionally unstable people
recode a124_04 (-5/-1=.), gen(emotionalunst)

*a124_05 Neighbours: Muslims
recode a124_05 (-5/-1=.), gen(muslims)

*a124_06 Neighbours: Immigrants/foreign workers
recode a124_06 (-5/-1=.), gen(immigrants)

*a124_07 Neighbours: People who have AIDS
recode a124_07 (-5/-1=.), gen(aids)

*a124_08 Neighbours: Drug addicts
recode a124_08 (-5/-1=.), gen(addicts)

*a124_09 Neighbours: Homosexuals
recode a124_09 (-5/-1=.), gen(homosexual)

*a124_10 Neighbours: Jews
*a124_11 Neighbours: Evangelists

*a124_12 Neighbours: People of a different religion
recode a124_12 (-5/-1=.), gen(diffreligion)

*a124_13 Neighbours: People of the same religion
recode a124_13 (-5/-1=.), gen(samereligion)

*a124_14 Neighbours: Militant minority
*a124_15 Neighbours: Zoroastrians


*a124_16 Neighbours: People not from country of origin
recode a124_16 (-5/-1=.), gen(foreigners)

*a124_17 Neighbours: Gypsies

*a124_18 Neighbours: Political Extremists
recode a124_18 (-5/-1=.), gen(polextremists)

*a124_19 Neighbours: Trafficants
*a124_20 Neighbours: Indians or Lebanese
*a124_21 Neighbours: Chinese or Philippine Chinese
*a124_22 Neighbours: Spiritists
*a124_23 Neighbours: Protestants

*a124_24 Neighbours: Christians
recode a124_24 (-5/-1=.), gen(christians)

*a124_25 Neighbours: Witchdoctors and related labels

*a124_26 Neighbours: Left wing extremists
recode a124_26 (-5/-1=.), gen(lwextreme)
*a124_27 Neighbours: Right wing extremists
recode a124_27 (-5/-1=.), gen(rwextreme)

local neighbours criminal race emotionalunst muslims immigrants aids addicts homosexual diffreligion samereligion foreigners polextremists christians lwextreme rwextreme 
foreach x of local neighbours {
	rename `x' nbrs_`x'
}

recode e033 (-5/0=.), gen(ideology)

recode g021 (4=1) (3=2) (2=3) (1=4) (-5/-1=.), gen(natidentity)

use "Data_Ben/data/collapse/WVS_EVS_collapse_survey_waves", clear
label var proud "National Pride"
label var tmorale "Tax Morale"
label var benefits "Benefit Morale"
label var bribecomp "Social Norms Against Bribing"
label var littermorale "Social Norms Against Littering"
label var drinkdrive "Social Norms Against Drunk Driving"

local indvar tmorale benefits bribecomp littermorale drinkdrive
foreach x of local indvar {
	forval e = 1/4 {
		pwcorr `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 0 & waves == `e', sig
		if `r(N)' != 0 {
			twoway lfit `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 0 & waves == `e' /// 
			 || scatter `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 0 & waves == `e' , msize(vsmall) mlabsize(vsmall) mcolor(maroon) msymbol(O) mlabtextstyle(tick_label) mlabcolor(maroon) mlabel(iso_23) ///
			 xtitle("National Pride") ylabel(, nogrid) graphr(fc(white)) note(`note') plotregion(margin(r+9))
			 graph save "Data_Ben/graphs/Swaves/`x'_EVS_wave_`e'", replace
		 }
	}
	forval w = 1/6 {
		pwcorr `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 1 & waves == `w', sig
		if `r(N)' != 0 {
			twoway lfit `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 1 & waves == `w' /// 
			 || scatter `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 1 & waves == `w' , msize(vsmall) mlabsize(vsmall) mcolor(maroon) msymbol(O) mlabtextstyle(tick_label) mlabcolor(maroon) mlabel(iso_23) ///
			 xtitle("National Pride") ylabel(, nogrid) graphr(fc(white)) note(`note') plotregion(margin(r+9))
			 graph save "Data_Ben/graphs/Swaves/`x'_WVS_wave_`w'", replace
		}
	}
}

use "Data_Ben/data/collapse/WVS_EVS_collapse_survey", clear

label var proud "National Pride"
label var tmorale "Tax Morale"
label var benefits "Benefit Morale"
label var bribecomp "Social Norms Against Bribing"
label var littermorale "Social Norms Against Littering"
label var drinkdrive "Social Norms Against Drunk Driving"

local indvar tmorale benefits bribecomp littermorale drinkdrive
foreach x of local indvar {
	pwcorr `x' proud if WVS == 1, sig
	twoway lfit `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 1 /// 
	 || scatter `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 1, msize(vsmall) mlabsize(vsmall) mcolor(maroon) msymbol(O) mlabtextstyle(tick_label) mlabcolor(maroon) mlabel(iso_23) ///
	 xtitle("National Pride") ylabel(, nogrid) graphr(fc(white)) note(`note') plotregion(margin(r+9))
	 graph save "Data_Ben/graphs/`x'_WVS", replace

 	pwcorr `x' proud if WVS == 0, sig
	twoway lfit `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 0 /// 
	 || scatter `x' proud if `x' != . & proud != . & WVS == 0, msize(vsmall) mlabsize(vsmall) mcolor(maroon) msymbol(O) mlabtextstyle(tick_label) mlabcolor(maroon) mlabel(iso_23) ///
	 xtitle("National Pride") ylabel(, nogrid) graphr(fc(white)) note(`note') plotregion(margin(r+9))
	 graph save "Data_Ben/graphs/`x'_EVS", replace
}
